Executable PennyLane:

import pennylane as qml
dev = qml.device('default.qubit', wires=1)
@qml.qnode(dev)
def circuit():
    qml.Hadamard(wires=0)
    return qml.expval(qml.PauliZ(0))
_p(circuit())   # ~0.0

The QNode runs the Hadamard on the default.qubit simulator and returns <Z>, which is 0 for the |+> state because it lies on the equator of the Bloch sphere.
